    <h1>Getting Started</h1>

    <h2 id="Installation">Installing Web Stories for WordPress</h2>

    <p>You can install the Web Stories WordPress plugin directly from within your WordPress admin or by manually downloading it from the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/web-stories/">WordPress.org plugin repository</a>. Follow the steps below to install the Web Stories for WordPress plugin:

    <ol>
      <li>In your WordPress admin, go to "Plugins" &rarr; "Add New".</li>
      <li>Search for "web stories" . You should see the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/web-stories/">Web Stories plugin</a> in the search results.</li>
      <li>Install and activate the Web Stories plugin.</li>
      <li>Click on the new "Stories" admin menu item to navigate to the Web Stories Dashboard.</li>
    </ol>

    <p><b>Note:</b> You need to be an administrator in order to be able to install plugins.</p>

    <h2>Finding your way around</h2>

    <p>With the Web Stories WordPress plugin, there are essentially two main applications you can access:</p>

    <ol>
      <li>
        <a href="{{ DOCS_BASE }}/getting-started/dashboard/">The Dashboard</a><br />
        Manage your stories, editor-related settings, and explore dozens of inspiring templates.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="{{ DOCS_BASE }}/getting-started/editor/">The Editor</a><br />
        Get started creating immersive stories using the feature-rich and easy-to-use editor.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <p><b>Tip:</b> Before diving right into it and creating your first story, learn more about <a href="https://creators.google/en-us/content-creation-guides/modern-storytelling-with-web-stories/web-story-taxonomy/">the Web Stories nomenclature</a> in this Google for Creators guide.</p>
